addr(bytes32).details: Gets ETH address for a labelhash (convenience function)

addr(bytes32,uint256).details: Gets an address record (with override priority)

params.labelhash: The labelhash to extend lock for
params.newExpiration: The new expiration timestamp (must be later than current)

getExpiration(bytes32).details: Gets the expiration timestamp for a labelhash

returns._0: uint256 The expiration timestamp (0 if not locked)

getLabel(bytes32).details: Returns the human-readable label for a labelhash

params.labelhash: The labelhash to get the label for

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Checks if operator is approved for owner

isExpired(bytes32).details: Checks if a labelhash is currently expired

returns._0: bool True if the labelhash is expired

owner(bytes32).details: Gets the owner of a labelhash

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setAddr(bytes32,address).details: Sets ETH address for a labelhash (convenience function)

setAddr(bytes32,uint256,bytes).details: Sets an address record for a specific labelhash

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Sets approval for an operator to manage all caller's labelhashes

params.approved: Whether to approve or revoke approval
params.operator: The address to approve or revoke approval for

setContenthash(bytes32,bytes).details: Sets content hash for a specific labelhash

setLabelhashRecord(string,address,uint25.details: Sets a complete record for a labelhash using parent + label pattern

params.coinTypes: Array of coin types for address records
params.label: The human-readable label for the subdomain (e.g., "alice", "subdomain")
params.newOwner: The new owner for the labelhash

setOwner(bytes32,address).details: Sets the owner of a labelhash Can only be called when the labelhash is in transfer mode (secure state)

setRecord(bytes32,address[],uint256[],st.details: Only the authorized owner or an approved operator can call this function.      The function allows updating the owner, text records, address records, and contenthash for a given labelhash.      To skip updating the owner or contenthash, pass an empty array for `newOwners` or `contentHashs` respectively.      Only one owner and one contenthash can be set at a time.

params.addresses: Array of address records to set, corresponding to `coinTypes`.
params.coinTypes: Array of coin types for address records to set.
params.contentHash_s: Array containing the new contenthash. If empty, the contenthash is not updated.
params.expiration_s: Array containing the new expiration. If empty, the expiration is not updated.
params.keys: Array of text record keys to set.
params.labelhash: The labelhash of the record to update.
params.newOwner_s: Array containing the new owner address. If empty, the owner is not updated.
params.values: Array of text record values to set, corresponding to `keys`.

setText(bytes32,string,string).details: Sets a text record for a specific labelhash

setRecord(bytes32,address[],uint256[],st.notice: Sets multiple records for a specific labelhash, including owner, text records, address records, and contenthash.
